The following document lists the steps for compiling Nek5000 on Blue Waters (BW)


1. Swap to pgi programing  environment, the only compiler for which Nek is wokring on BW

module swap PrgEnv-cray PrgEnv-pgi



2. Use the makenek file which has been provided for compiling. 
   
You also need to change the makenek.inc in ~/nek5_svn/trunk/nek/
replace the existing makenek.inc with makenek.inc.pgi 
(and obviouslly change its name to makenek.inc)   



3. After the above changes have been done you should be able to 
   compile Nek5000



  





